 German <b>Kranke</b>: from Low German <i>Kraneke</i> ‘crane’, applied to someone thought to resemble the bird in some way, or a nickname for a poor physical specimen, from Middle High German <i>kranc</i> ‘sickly, ailing’."]},{"name":"Cran","meanings":["Scottish (Aberdeenshire): variant of English   Crane  .","Dutch: variant of <b>Kraan</b> or one of its variants, such as <b>Craane</b> and   Krane  ."]},{"name":"Cornforth","meanings":["English (North Yorkshire and Durham): habitational name from Cornforth in County Durham, named with Old English <i>corn</i>, a metathesized form of <i>cron</i>, <i>cran</i> ‘crane’ (see   Crane  ) + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Crane was born in 1305, in Wood Norton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Crane, was 31 and his mother, Alice Mollington, was 26. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Alice Berry."},"et":{"1305–":"1305–Surnud","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1309–Female":"1309–Surnud","1338–Female":"1338–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1274–Male":"1274–Surnud","1279–1305":"1279–1305","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1279":"1279","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1274":"1274","1309":"1309","Woodnorton, Norfolk, England":"Wood Norton, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chilton, Suffolk, England":"Chilton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1305–":"1305–Kuollut","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1309–Female":"1309–Kuollut","1338–Female":"1338–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1274–Male":"1274–Kuollut","1279–1305":"1279–1305","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1279":"1279","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1274":"1274","1309":"1309","Woodnorton, Norfolk, England":"Wood Norton, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chilton, Suffolk, England":"Chilton, 